STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Tyrone VALENTINE, Appellant. No. ED 106729 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION TWO. Filed: April 16, 2019
Application for Transfer Denied September 3, 2019 ATTORNEYS FOR APPELLANT: Tyrone Valentine, Pro Se, #23006-044, Ste. Genevieve County Jail, #5 Basler Drive, Ste. Genevieve, MO 63670. ATTORNEYS FOR RESPONDENT: Eric Schmitt, Attorney General, Evan J. Buchheim, Asst. Attorney General, P. O. Box 899, Jefferson City, MO 65102-0899. Before Philip M. Hess, P.J. and Robert G. Dowd, Jr. and Mary K. Hoff, JJ.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Tyrone Valentine appeals from the judgment of the trial court denying his Rule 29.07(d) motion to withdraw his guilty pleas. Finding no error, we affirm.

An opinion would have no precedential value nor serve any jurisprudential purpose. The parties have been furnished with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this order pursuant to Rule 84.16(b).
